<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49378">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49378">
Larvae of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Isocladius" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Cricotopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Isocladius) subsp. subgenus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" species="speciosus" subGenus="Isocladius" subSpecies="subgenus">subgenus Isocladius</taxonomicName>
are widespread in mountain lakes in the Alps (
<bibRefCitation author="Boggero, Angela" journalOrPublisher="Redia" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" pagination="35 - 45" refId="B5460475" refString="Boggero, Angela, 2018. Macroinvertebrates of Italian mountainlakes. Redia 101: 35 - 45" title="Macroinvertebrates of Italian mountainlakes" volume="101" year="2018">Boggero 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and the Tatra Mountains (
<bibRefCitation author="Bitusik, Peter" journalOrPublisher="Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" pagination="S 191 - S 201" refId="B5460441" refString="Bitusik, Peter, Svitok, Marek, Kolosta, Peter, Hubkova, Marta, 2006. Classification of the Tatra Mountain lakes (Slovakia) using chironomids (Diptera, Chironomidae). Biologia 61 (18): S191 - S201" title="Classification of the Tatra Mountain lakes (Slovakia) using chironomids (Diptera, Chironomidae)" volume="61" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bitušík">Bitusik</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
), but species composition is insufficiently known due to identification difficulties. 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (I.) speciosus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus" subGenus="I.">C. (I.) speciosus</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="sylvestris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378">sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, members of which are mostly eurythermic and euryoecious. There is a considerable gap in the knowledge of the species' ecologies. 
<bibRefCitation author="Langton, P. H." journalOrPublisher="World Biodiversity Database, CD-ROM Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="49378" refId="B5460898" refString="Langton, P. H., Visser, H., 2003. Chironomidae exuviae. A key to pupal exuviae of the West Palaearctic Region. Interactive identification system for the European limnofauna (IISEL). World Biodiversity Database, CD-ROM Series" title="Chironomidae exuviae. A key to pupal exuviae of the West Palaearctic Region. Interactive identification system for the European limnofauna (IISEL)" year="2003">Langton and Visser (2003)</bibRefCitation>
mention its occurrence in ponds, lakes and running waters.
</paragraph>
